description:
Expand the label view to include upstream dependencies (blockers) of labeled issues.

## Requirements
- Given a set of labeled issues, traverse upstream to find all blocking issues
- Default depth: 3 levels of dependencies
- Configurable depth via `d` key (cycle 1 â†’ 2 â†’ 3 â†’ All â†’ 1)
- Direction: upstream (blockers) by default
- Mark expanded issues distinctly from directly-labeled issues

## Algorithm
```
func expandDependencies(labeledIssues []Issue, depth int) []Issue {
    seen := map[string]bool{}
    queue := labeledIssues  // BFS from labeled issues

    for level := 0; level < depth; level++ {
        nextQueue := []Issue{}
        for _, issue := range queue {
            for _, dep := range issue.Dependencies {
                if !seen[dep.ID] {
                    seen[dep.ID] = true
                    nextQueue = append(nextQueue, dep)
                }
            }
        }
        queue = nextQueue
    }

    return allDiscoveredIssues
}
```

## Data Model
- Track whether each issue is "primary" (has label) or "context" (pulled in via deps)
- Store current depth setting in view state

