- `pkg/analysis/` (may add helper for dependency traversal)
- Consider reusing graph traversal from existing analysis code

Add keybindings to quickly jump between unreviewed items.

**Keybindings:**
- `]` = Jump to next unreviewed item
- `[` = Jump to previous unreviewed item

**Implementation:**
```go
func (m *ReviewDashboardModel) jumpToNextUnreviewed() {
    startIdx := m.cursor + 1
    for i := startIdx; i < len(m.flatNodes); i++ {
        if m.flatNodes[i].Issue.ReviewStatus == "" || 
           m.flatNodes[i].Issue.ReviewStatus == "unreviewed" {
            m.cursor = i
            m.ensureVisible()
            return
        }
    }
    // Wrap around to beginning
    for i := 0; i < startIdx; i++ {
        if m.flatNodes[i].Issue.ReviewStatus == "" || 
           m.flatNodes[i].Issue.ReviewStatus == "unreviewed" {
            m.cursor = i
            m.ensureVisible()
            return
        }
    }
    // No unreviewed items found - flash message?
}
```

**Behavior:**
- Wraps around at end/beginning
- Shows message if no unreviewed items remain
- Ensures jumped-to item is visible (adjusts scroll)

